      "message": "nit: not sure if it\u0027s the doc or the naming, but this type is a little confusing.\n\n1. This type does not update a Graph. Graph.updateFrom uses this type to update itself.\n\n2. From the perspective of this package, this type is a \"Repo.\" However, that name is very overloaded, so maybe something like RepoData or RepoInfo or RepoImpl.\n\n3. Maybe add some doc to explain how the methods interact with each other. E.g. \"Branches returns the branch heads as of the last call to Update.\"\n\n4. Mention that methods may not be called concurrently. (This is already true for repoUpdater, and in another comment I mentioned that gitstoreUpdater.mtx can be removed.)",
